					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12264474#post-4318233</guid>
				<title>JS Site Crit Team</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12264474/scp-1204#post-4318233</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2019 18:02:48 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ManyMeats</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2104082</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is the kind of gross that I like. I don't actually recall having read the original so I can't comment on whether or not you did the spirit of that piece justice, but what I can say is that I enjoyed this.</p> <p>I'm not sure the inclusion of the homeless/vagrant population did anything for me or added anything to the rest of the story but I have to allow for the possibility I just simply didn't 'get it'. This one small section aside, the article was well written and enjoyable from beginning to end. The letters at the end lacked context but they did so constructively and allowed me to better absorb the angle of a generally faceless disease.</p> <p>Great work on a solid +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
